rComments: Though this was a difficult class, I absolutely enjoyed her class. Her lectures are clear and detailed and she solves a bunch of examples. She always wants to make sure her students are understanding. She is very accessible out of class and her office hours are big help. I recommend her 100%!!

She is a very caring prof that wants you to understand but she didn't deliver her lectures in a way that helped. Her exams were easy and test questions were very similar to her assignments. Get the textbook .Try to avoid her, but if you're stuck with her, just do the assg and go to help centre cause you'll probably not learn much from her lectures.

She definitely care about her students and wants everyone to do well, but I didn't find her all that helpful in terms of explaining concepts. She mostly copied down the notes (which were provided on Brightspace) and repeated herself. Reading the notes outside of class is the only reason I managed to understand what was going on.
teacherRatingTags: ['Caring', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Prof. Sohrabi is a good professor. She's kind, approachable and her lectures are to the point (that is, she won't add lots of useless stuff to the board). On the cons side, she has trouble explaining the why of things and complex ideas. Also, her office hours are not very useful: she'll say a few words and ask you to try the problem by yourself.
I like her. She teaches the material effectively and see always encourage students to come and ask their questions during the office hours.
She's a very good professor. Knows exactly what she's doing and her exams are not really difficult.

Her lectures are unbearable unfortunately. You'll have more luck studying the midterms and using khan khademy. She also is condescending when you go to get your exam and ask her questions about it. I don't think there are many profs available though that are better at OTTAWA U. Pick your poison :)
Cares about her students and wants everyone to do well. I enjoyed her Class!
Very bad at explaining and her accent doesn't help at all
All she does is reading off the notes she's given. Not a difficult course, but she doesn't 'explain' any concepts.
Very good professor, wants her students to succeed. Clear and concise notes and examples. Textbook is necessary for assignments.

A really nice professor who honestly wants you to do well in the course. She gave you A LOT of chances to improve your grade which was incredibly helpful. She has a tendency to repeat herself a lot, but English isn't her first language, so it's understandable. Follow the lecture notes and do the online questions and you'll be fine

Dr Sohrabi is a very sweet woman. It was a bit difficult to understand her sometimes during the lectures, but she always encouraged people to come to office hours if you needed extra help. The midterm and exam were both fair, and assignments were easy. Overall a pretty decent course!
She is one of the best professor I have ever had !! Take Stat course with her..
She is AMAZING! She really cares about her students, and she is definitely there to help you. Overall, great  prof!

VERY unclear during lectures, answers questions by repeating the same unhelpful information. Basically learned all the material at home via Khan academy. Only give 5 assignments and has a midterm + final, so it's an easy class (material isn't too hard). Pronunciations/etc. can be hilarious though: Ex. "Flip a coin and you might get head."
